                        <tr class="data" onmouseover="return overlib('\r&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Conference on CYber physiCaL systems, iOt and sensors Networks (CYCLONE 2015) &lt;/div&gt;\r&lt;div class=&quot;text&quot;&gt;Call for Papers&lt;br /&gt;\r\r-------------------------------------&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rInternational Conference on CYber physiCaL systems, iOt and sensors Networks (CYCLONE 2015)&lt;br /&gt;\r\rRome, Italy, 26 October, 2015&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rhttp://cyclone-iot.org&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rScope&lt;br /&gt;\r\rThe International Conference on CYber physiCaL systems, iOt and sensors Networks (CYCLONE 2015) will focus on theoretical, simulation and experimental activities related to Wireless Sensors and Actuators Networks, Cyber Physical Systems, IoT, Platforms, Sensor Cloud. Contributions from federated and large scale experiments will be highly appreciated, particularly the ones showing the applicability of open hardware/software solutions. Key persons from the manufacturing sectors showing the relevance of sensing devices and specific hardware components will be invited together with people illustrating more and more &amp;quot;softwarized&amp;quot; and de-verticalized solutions.&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rConference topics&lt;br /&gt;\r\rCYCLONE aims at bringing together researchers from academia and industry to identify and discuss technical challenges, exchange novel ideas, explore enabling technologies, and report latest research efforts that cover a variety of topics including, but not limited to:&lt;br /&gt;\r\r- Cyber-physical systems: theory, tools, applications, testbeds and field deployments&lt;br /&gt;\r\r- IoT platforms: Theory tools, testbeds and field deployments&lt;br /&gt;\r\r- Sensor Network applications: Transportation, energy, water, agriculture, ecology/environment, supply chains, medical, assistive technology, social networks, robotics&lt;br /&gt;\r\r- Topics related to Wireless Sensors and Actuators Networks, Cyber Physical Systems, IoT, Platforms and Sensor Cloud: Security, privacy control, optimization, machine learning, game theory, mobile and cloud computing, model-based design, verification, data mining, signal processing, human-in-the-loop, shared or supervisory control&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rOrganizing Committee&lt;br /&gt;\r\rGeneral Co-Chairs&lt;br /&gt;\r\rStefano Giordano, University of Pisa, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\rPeriklis Chatzimisios, Alexander TEI of Thessaloniki, Greece&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rTechnical Program Co-Chairs&lt;br /&gt;\r\rHonggang Wang, UMass Dartmouth, USA&lt;br /&gt;\r\rAthanasios C. Iossifides, Alexander TEI of Thessaloniki, Greece&lt;br /&gt;\r\rGennaro Boggia, Politehnico di Barri, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rPublicity and Social Media Chairs&lt;br /&gt;\r\rDaniele Mazzei, Research Center Â“E.PiaggioÂ”, University of Pisa, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\rAlessio Botta, Universita degli Studi di Napoli &amp;quot;Federico II&amp;quot;, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\rSyed Zaidi, University of Leeds, UK&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rWorkshops Chair&lt;br /&gt;\r\rKan Zheng, Beijing University of Posts &amp;amp; Telecommunications, China&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rSpecial Session Chair&lt;br /&gt;\r\rToktam Mahmoodi, King\'s College London, UK&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rSponsorship &amp;amp; Exhibits Chair&lt;br /&gt;\r\rLuca Foschini, University of Bologna, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rPanels Chair&lt;br /&gt;\r\rRosario G. Garroppo, University of Pisa, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rTutorial Chair&lt;br /&gt;\r\rCharalabos Skianis, University of the Aegean, Greece&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rDemos Chair&lt;br /&gt;\r\rDavide Adami, CNIT, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rPosters and PhD Track Chair&lt;br /&gt;\r\rChristian Callegari, University of Pisa, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rLocal Chair&lt;br /&gt;\r\rMichele Pagano, University of Pisa, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&g