                        <tr class="data" onmouseover="return overlib('\r&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Summer School on Internet of Things (Rome, Italy)&lt;/div&gt;\r&lt;div class=&quot;text&quot;&gt; &amp;quot;IOT 360&amp;quot; SUMMER SCHOOL ON THE INTERNET OF THINGS&lt;br /&gt;\r\r Oct 27-30, 2015 - Rome, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\r http://iot-360.eu/2015/co-located-events/&lt;br /&gt;\r\r &lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rDescription&lt;br /&gt;\r\rIn the last decade the Internet of Things (IoT) paradigm has slowly but steadily and increasingly permeated what researchers and engineers study and build. However, a ‘Killer’ IoT application is still missing so far. The ‘IoT-360’ Summer School will demonstrate what it takes to deliver an IoT-based product from scratch. To do so, the School will be divided into two strongly coupled parts.&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rThe first part consists of lectures and tutorials, as well as a panel discussion where School participants will gain relevant knowledge and development skills. Based on the last year School success and feedback the lectures are upgraded with the topics on power and connectivity related challenges, as well as more detailed tutorial on hands-on will be provided. During the second part the school participants grouped in teams will implement their own IoT projects relying on knowledge gained during the School and on IoT hardware/software that will be made available. Finally, for the attendees, there will be a chance to “pitch and sell” their projects developed during the “IoT Hackathon”.&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rGoals&lt;br /&gt;\r\r*Demonstrate what it takes to deliver an IoT product from scratch;&lt;br /&gt;\r\r*Survey the most relevant research domains;&lt;br /&gt;\r\r*Get in touch with IoT (hands-on);&lt;br /&gt;\r\r*Interact with distinguished scholars and world-known experts;&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rWho should attend?&lt;br /&gt;\r\r*(post)(under) graduate students;&lt;br /&gt;\r\r*Post Doctoral Fellows;&lt;br /&gt;\r\r*Academic Professionals;&lt;br /&gt;\r\r*Research Scientists and Engineers;&lt;br /&gt;\r\r*All those who wish to be introduced and apply IoT in their professional/amateur projects;&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rConfirmed Lecturers&lt;br /&gt;\r\rPayam Barnaghi – University of Surrey, UK&lt;br /&gt;\r\rRahul Bhattacharyya – Massachusetts Institute of Technology, USA&lt;br /&gt;\r\rDavid Bordonada – Libelium, Spain&lt;br /&gt;\r\rClaudio Carnevali – openPicus / Smartables, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\rPeriklis Chatzimisios – Alexander TEI of Thessaloniki, Greece&lt;br /&gt;\r\rFahim Kawsar – Alcatel-Lucent Bell Labs, Belgium&lt;br /&gt;\r\rAndrey Somov – CREATE-NET, Italy&lt;br /&gt;\r\rThomas Watteyne – INRIA, France&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rOrganization Committee&lt;br /&gt;\r\rAndrey Somov (CREATE-NET, Italy)&lt;br /&gt;\r\rRaffaele Giaffreda (CREATE-NET, Italy)&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rImportant Dates&lt;br /&gt;\r\rEarly registration: Jul 30, 2015&lt;br /&gt;\r\rRegistration deadline: Sept 30, 2015&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;br /&gt;\r\rUseful Links&lt;br /&gt;\r\rSummer School: http://iot-360.eu/2015/co-located-events/&lt;br /&gt;\r\rProgram: http://iot-360.eu/2015/co-located-events/summer-school-program/&lt;br /&gt;\r\rRegistration: http://services.eai.eu/registration.login/IoT%20Summer%20School/2015&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;/div&gt;\r\r',TEXTCOLOR,'#000000',FGCOLOR,'#f0f0f0',BGCOLOR,'#333333',BORDER,2,DELAY,300,WIDTH,500);" onmouseout="nd();">
