rie, (Paris 6) France in 1992, and 1994 respectively. He received his PhD degree from the University of Versailles, France, in 1998. He was an Assistant Professor at the University of Orsay (Paris 11) and University of Pierre et Marie Curie (Paris 6), in 1998 and 1999 respectively. He was an Associate Professor at the University of Versailles from 2000 to 2011. He is currently full Professor at the University of Paris 13 since 2011.&lt;br /&gt;\r\r&lt;/div&gt;\r\r',TEXTCOLOR,'#000000',FGCOLOR,'#f0f0f0',BGCOLOR,'#333333',BORDER,2,DELAY,300,WIDTH,500);" onmouseout="nd();">
